till I get to the bottom of it.

757
00:53:41,906 --> 00:53:46,104
Do me a favor, Bobby.
Go back, buy me one more day.

758
00:53:54,218 --> 00:53:57,085
We organize search parties.
We work with the families.

759
00:53:57,254 --> 00:53:58,915
We work with the cops.

760
00:53:59,090 --> 00:54:01,854
But most of all, we're just
a bunch of parents, you know?

761
00:54:02,026 --> 00:54:05,052
Concerned parents. Because of
that, because of who we are...

762
00:54:05,229 --> 00:54:09,063
...we get in tight with the moms in
a way that's different from the police.

763
00:54:09,233 --> 00:54:11,428
- You know what I'm saying.
- You were in on that...

764
00:54:11,602 --> 00:54:13,900
...Sandra Howard thing
in Bayonne, right?

765
00:54:14,071 --> 00:54:16,198
- Am I remembering that right?
- Yeah, we helped.

766
00:54:17,341 --> 00:54:19,104
The mother got locked up
on that one.

767
00:54:19,276 --> 00:54:20,800
Like I said, we helped.

768
00:54:24,081 --> 00:54:26,675
Well, I don't want you jumping
to conclusions about Brenda.

769
00:54:26,851 --> 00:54:28,910
No. No, that wouldn't
serve anybody.

770
00:54:29,086 --> 00:54:30,678
And I call the shots.

771
00:54:30,855 --> 00:54:33,153
Yes. It goes without saying
that we'd cooperate...

772
00:54:33,324 --> 00:54:36,725
No, no, no. I call the shots.

773
00:54:39,030 --> 00:54:41,191
Now, I got something
in my head...

774
00:54:41,365 --> 00:54:44,823
...that would play out better coming
from somebody other than me.

775
00:54:45,002 --> 00:54:47,197
I'll let your people
do whatever it is they do...

776
00:54:47,371 --> 00:54:52,172
...but with all due respect, you'll be
working for me and not with me.

777
00:54:52,877 --> 00:54:54,674
If that's unacceptable,
all you do is...

778
00:54:54,845 --> 00:54:58,804
You tell us where you wanna go,
and we will help you get there.

779
00:55:00,718 --> 00:55:03,186
Yeah, all right. Okay, then.

780
00:55:03,454 --> 00:55:04,944
<i>We just want the boy back</i>.

781
00:55:06,023 --> 00:55:09,720
Have you or any of your people
ever been out to Freedomland?

782
00:55:10,761 --> 00:55:13,594
You guys still hazing
your rookies there?

783
00:55:14,532 --> 00:55:15,965
Yeah.

784
00:55:21,238 --> 00:55:24,730
Detective Council here brought us up
to speed from the police point of view.

785
00:55:24,909 --> 00:55:27,571
But we are not here as cops.
We're here as parents.

786
00:55:27,745 --> 00:55:29,906
We're here because
we all have children too.

787
00:55:30,081 --> 00:55:31,378
What happened to your son...

788
00:55:31,549 --> 00:55:34,143
...could have happened
to any of our own children, okay?

789
00:55:34,318 --> 00:55:36,149
Okay.

790
00:55:36,454 --> 00:55:38,979
Now, this is Marie. And Lewis.

791
00:55:39,523 --> 00:55:42,390
This is Elaine. This is Tina.

792
00:55:42,560 --> 00:55:44,118
Elaine is her mom.

793
00:55:44,295 --> 00:55:45,887
Who's Kent?

794
00:55:46,063 --> 00:55:49,692
He's the first boy we ever
tried to find. Ten years ago.

795
00:55:49,867 --> 00:55:51,960
We've been helping find kids
ever since.

796
00:55:52,136 --> 00:55:54,798
- Did you find Kent?
- Brenda?

797
00:55:54,972 --> 00:55:57,236
Would you like our help?

798
00:55:59,276 --> 00:56:00,538
Okay.

799
00:56:00,711 --> 00:56:02,941
Good. Good.

800
00:56:03,981 --> 00:56:07,974
Okay, now, first off, what I need
is to hear from you what happened.

801
00:56:08,152 --> 00:56:10,848
I can't. I can't say that.
I told the police everything.

802
00:56:11,021 --> 00:56:13,080
- I told them...
- I know, I know, I know, I know.

803
00:56:13,257 --> 00:56:16,852
It's just... Look, like I said, they
have their priorities and we have ours.

804
00:56:17,027 --> 00:56:19,723
One more time, Brenda, and
I wouldn't put you through this...

805
00:56:19,897 --> 00:56:22,957
No. No. I can't. I just...

806
00:56:25,536 --> 00:56:26,935
No.

807
00:56:30,007 --> 00:56:31,599
Okay.

808
00:56:34,111 --> 00:56:36,409
Okay. I understand.

809
00:56:36,580 --> 00:56:39,174
We'll just go with the police report
if you want.

810
00:56:40,151 --> 00:56:43,882
Okay. Now first thing,
we come to the question head-on.

811
00:56:45,956 --> 00:56:47,924
Where is your son?

812
00:56:50,494 --> 00:56:52,689
Right? Where do we look?

813
00:56:52,863 --> 00:56:55,559
Where do we look?
What is your gut feeling, Brenda?

814
00:56:55,733 --> 00:56:58,361
- He took off in a car.
- Okay, well, let's say your son...

815
00:56:58,536 --> 00:57:01,835
...woke up. Let's say the guy
realized he had a kid in the car...

816
00:57:02,006 --> 00:57:05,032
...sooner rather than later.
So let's keep it within a mile.

817
00:57:05,209 --> 00:57:08,076
But the fact of the matter is,
it's been almost 24 hours.

818
00:57:08,245 --> 00:57:10,372
So the odds of him still
wandering the streets...

819
00:57:10,548 --> 00:57:13,278
...not getting picked up by now
are not so good.

820
00:57:13,751 --> 00:57:16,379
Now, we looked at the map
earlier today, and we came up...

821
00:57:16,554 --> 00:57:19,648
...with four possibilities where a kid
could conceivably get lost...

822
00:57:19,824 --> 00:57:22,884
...or hide out for a whole day
or night and not get noticed.

823
00:57:23,060 --> 00:57:25,585
And then we drove around,
we eliminated three of them.

824
00:57:25,763 --> 00:57:29,460
This is a golf course.
This is a cemetery.

825
00:57:29,633 --> 00:57:31,328
This is a ball field.

826
00:57:31,502 --> 00:57:34,437
There's no cover, no place
to hide, if that's what he's doing.

827
00:57:34,605 --> 00:57:37,233
Which leaves us...

828
00:57:37,541 --> 00:57:39,168
...Freedomland.

829
00:57:39,743 --> 00:57:41,540
Freedomland?

830
00:57:41,712 --> 00:57:44,613
It's an old state children's home
in the back of Cotter's Woods.

831
00:57:44,782 --> 00:57:47,717
It was like a foundling asylum,
like some kind of a youth house.

832
00:57:47,885 --> 00:57:50,581
- It's been shut since the '50s.
- It's not far from Armstrong.

833
00:57:50,754 --> 00:57:54,246
- Cody could have...
- Yeah, okay. Okay.

834
00:57:58,829 --> 00:58:00,558
So Freedomland?

835
00:58:00,731 --> 00:58:02,926
I feel good about Freedomland
for this one.

836
00:58:03,100 --> 00:58:05,034
- Okay.
- Okay.

837
00:58:05,202 --> 00:58:06,931
Freedomland it is.

838
00:58:07,104 --> 00:58:10,164
- You're coming too, right?
- Absolutely.

839
00:58:57,388 --> 00:58:58,855
What the hell's all this?

840
00:58:59,023 --> 00:59:01,457
- I just need to get her to Freedomland.
- And you will.

841
00:59:01,625 --> 00:59:04,219
It's not gonna work if you
make a beeline for it. Trust me.

842
00:59:04,395 --> 00:59:06,693
Meanwhile, we have a little problem.

843
00:59:08,699 --> 00:59:11,668
Look, you're here,
you might as well get out.

844
00:59:11,835 --> 00:59:13,826
Just let us open the door.
How about that?

845
00:59:14,004 --> 00:59:15,699
Excuse me, ladies.

846
00:59:20,444 --> 00:59:22,571
Hey, Brenda. How you doing?

847
00:59:41,632 --> 00:59:46,467
Heavenly father, we ask for your
blessing and guiding hand today...

848
00:59:47,538 --> 00:59:49,972
...as we send these volunteers down...

849
00:59:50,474 --> 00:59:54,342
...to help the mother of Cody Martin
find her child...

850
00:59:54,511 --> 00:59:56,706
...and safely bring him home.

851
00:59:56,880 --> 00:59:59,371
And we ask for the courage
and fortitude...

852
00:59:59,550 --> 01:00:03,145
...to see this task successfully done.

853
01:00:03,320 --> 01:00:05,982
In the name of the Father,
and of the Son...

854
01:00:06,156 --> 01:00:08,750
...and of the Holy Spirit. Amen.

855
01:00:08,926 --> 01:00:10,689
Amen.

856
01:01:38,015 --> 01:01:39,539
Cody!

857
01:01:39,716 --> 01:01:43,049
- Cody!
- Cody!

858
01:01:43,220 --> 01:01:45,154
- Cody!
- Cody!

859
01:01:45,322 --> 01:01:48,587
- Cody!
- Cody!

860
01:01:49,226 --> 01:01:51,786
- Cody!
- Cody!

861
01:01:51,962 --> 01:01:54,624
So where's her bug bands?

862
