904
01:06:17,728 --> 01:06:20,925
So I want you to stay in here
and wait for us, okay?

905
01:06:21,498 --> 01:06:22,988
What are you doing?

906
01:06:23,166 --> 01:06:25,134
Just wait for us.

907
01:06:32,242 --> 01:06:34,472
I can't be alone.

908
01:06:50,660 --> 01:06:52,992
I swear to God,
I feel like they're still here.

909
01:06:56,032 --> 01:06:57,659
I tell you, when...

910
01:06:57,834 --> 01:07:00,302
When they finally padlocked
this place, it was...

911
01:07:00,904 --> 01:07:03,668
It was like shutting down hell.

912
01:07:05,409 --> 01:07:10,142
Do you have any idea
of the generations of children...

913
01:07:10,313 --> 01:07:12,577
...who suffered in here?

914
01:07:13,250 --> 01:07:15,013
Thousands.

915
01:07:16,219 --> 01:07:20,053
Thousands who were neglected...

916
01:07:21,158 --> 01:07:23,490
...and abused...

917
01:07:23,927 --> 01:07:25,952
...forgotten.

918
01:07:27,063 --> 01:07:29,088
Just...

919
01:07:29,266 --> 01:07:31,496
Just wasted.

920
01:08:28,825 --> 01:08:31,385
<i>Even your own family turns on you</i>
<i>after a while</i>.

921
01:08:31,561 --> 01:08:33,552
You come downstairs,
the other kids are like:

922
01:08:33,730 --> 01:08:36,460
"Mommy, are you gonna
be sad today?"

923
01:08:37,567 --> 01:08:40,035
That's the only thing that can
bring you back to some...

924
01:08:40,203 --> 01:08:42,296
...charade of normal life,
when it hits you...

925
01:08:42,472 --> 01:08:46,408
...what you're doing to your
other kids, to your marriage.

926
01:08:47,077 --> 01:08:50,911
But with me, I couldn't even
rally for that. I couldn't fake it.

927
01:08:51,748 --> 01:08:55,548
This bastard, Jimmy,
he took away my life.

