elbow room in here, huh?

1389
01:41:02,343 --> 01:41:04,436
So they got you
in protective custody, huh?

1390
01:41:04,612 --> 01:41:06,512
On suicide watch too.

1391
01:41:07,215 --> 01:41:09,183
It's just standard procedure.

1392
01:41:13,087 --> 01:41:16,113
You know, you aren't the only person
I got to visit in here today.

1393
01:41:16,291 --> 01:41:18,054
My son, Jason...

1394
01:41:19,227 --> 01:41:22,219
...he's over in the state wing
doing two to four for armed robbery.

1395
01:41:22,397 --> 01:41:23,921
No.

1396
01:41:24,098 --> 01:41:26,191
- Used my gun too.
- Oh, no.

1397
01:41:26,367 --> 01:41:27,959
Yeah.

1398
01:41:28,303 --> 01:41:30,134
All my friends say to me:

1399
01:41:30,305 --> 01:41:33,900
"Lorenzo, it ain't your fault
that boy landed where he did.

1400
01:41:34,075 --> 01:41:36,737
He got to take responsibility
for that his own self.

1401
01:41:36,911 --> 01:41:40,074
I ain't seen no pacifier in his mouth
the last 10 years."

1402
01:41:40,248 --> 01:41:43,979
Well, between you and me,
it is my fault.

1403
01:41:44,786 --> 01:41:48,654
I do feel responsible
because the kind of man he is...

1404
01:41:48,823 --> 01:41:51,587
...is the kind of man
I showed him how to be.

1405
01:41:51,759 --> 01:41:54,227
High all the time.

1406
01:41:54,395 --> 01:41:57,296
Selfish. Out of control.

1407
01:41:57,465 --> 01:41:59,524
I was never there
on a day-to-day basis.

1408
01:41:59,701 --> 01:42:02,966
And when I was,
I was fighting with his moms.

1409
01:42:04,739 --> 01:42:07,674
Yeah, well, that's who I was.

1410
01:42:08,409 --> 01:42:10,377
I'm so sorry.

1411
01:42:12,647 --> 01:42:14,512
Back then...

1412
01:42:14,949 --> 01:42:17,213
...I just didn't give a shit.

1413
01:42:17,886 --> 01:42:19,183
Now Jason's in prison...

1414
01:42:19,721 --> 01:42:23,851
...and he'll probably be in and out
of prison the rest of his life.

1415
01:42:24,125 --> 01:42:25,990
It's kind of late in the game...

1416
01:42:26,160 --> 01:42:28,560
...but all I wanna do now
is be there for him.

1417
01:42:31,399 --> 01:42:33,196
But with kids...

1418
01:42:33,368 --> 01:42:37,634
...no matter what you did or how bad
you think you messed up...

1419
01:42:37,805 --> 01:42:41,400
...God always finds a way
to give you another shot at it.

1420
01:42:41,576 --> 01:42:44,272
It might not be
with that particular child, but...

1421
01:42:47,615 --> 01:42:50,778
What I'm trying to say, Brenda...

1422
01:42:50,985 --> 01:42:54,785
...is that God's grace
is sort of, like, retroactive.

1423
01:42:54,956 --> 01:42:58,722
So every little kid out there
is Jason for me now.

1424
01:42:59,394 --> 01:43:02,727
And, no, they're not my blood,
but I can live with that.

1425
01:43:02,897 --> 01:43:05,832
And I'm happy. My life is good.

1426
01:43:09,103 --> 01:43:11,094
There's a lot of young women
in here, Brenda.

1427
01:43:11,272 --> 01:43:15,606
Some of them are good mothers,
some ain't. But they all need help.

1428
01:43:15,777 --> 01:43:20,373
On visitors' day, in the nursery,
even in prenatal.

1429
01:43:20,548 --> 01:43:23,108
And the warden in here
is an old running buddy of mine...

1430
01:43:23,284 --> 01:43:24,615
I love you.

1431
01:43:24,986 --> 01:43:26,283
What?

1432
01:43:26,454 --> 01:43:29,685
I love you for the way
you talk to me.

1433
01:43:30,124 --> 01:43:32,251
I've loved you
for the way you talk to me...

1434
01:43:32,427 --> 01:43:34,759
...ever since I first met you
in the hospital.

1435
01:43:36,431 --> 01:43:38,160
I wish I had your heart.

1436
01:43:42,604 --> 01:43:47,667
Look, I don't know if your lawyer
is gonna do a plea bargain...

1437
01:43:47,842 --> 01:43:50,367
...or whatever,
or if you're going to trial.

1438
01:43:50,545 --> 01:43:53,981
But you'll still be a young woman.
Lots of things that you can...

1439
01:43:59,320 --> 01:44:02,118
I'll... I'll...
I'll come see you.

1440
01:44:02,757 --> 01:44:04,122
Brenda...

1441
01:44:04,292 --> 01:44:07,125
...reach out to people in here,
all right?

1442
01:44:32,620 --> 01:44:34,611
Jas, how you doing?

1443
01:44:34,789 --> 01:44:36,814
Wasn't you just here
on Tuesday, man?

1444
01:44:37,859 --> 01:44:39,224
You want me to leave?

1445
01:44:40,461 --> 01:44:42,986
No, it's all good.
It's Christmas in July.

1446
01:44:44,132 --> 01:44:46,692
So like I said,
how you doing, kid?

1447
01:44:47,035 --> 01:44:49,663
You know, the Aryan Nation
was asking me to hook up...

1448
01:44:49,837 --> 01:44:53,466
...but I was a little bit nervous about
the whole initiation thing, you know?

1449
01:45:01,015 --> 01:45:03,848
Hey, Dad, you..? You okay?

1450
01:45:06,187 --> 01:45:07,779
Yeah.

1451
01:45:08,923 --> 01:45:10,754
Yeah, I'm good.

1452
01:45:12,293 --> 01:45:14,022
I'm real good.

1453
01:45:22,503 --> 01:45:25,267
- So, what you think?
- I was looking at that.

1454
01:45:25,440 --> 01:45:27,101
What's going on with you?

1455
01:45:27,275 --> 01:45:29,641
You know, out there
roughnecking.

1456
01:45:29,811 --> 01:45:33,303
- So you fell off your bed.
- Yeah, right...

1457
01:45:52,567 --> 01:45:55,035
I thought you should see this.

1458
01:45:57,205 --> 01:45:58,536
Hey.

1459
01:46:01,809 --> 01:46:04,277
You know that thing
with the carjacker?

1460
01:46:05,012 --> 01:46:08,539
I know I'm supposed to find it
in my heart to forgive.

1461
01:46:08,716 --> 01:46:10,206
But...

1462
01:46:12,053 --> 01:46:14,453
And her with Billy.

1463
01:46:14,622 --> 01:46:16,852
I mean, he wasn't getting none
from me, so...

1464
01:46:19,360 --> 01:46:24,627
But, Lorenzo, did he have anything
to do with hurting that child?

1465
01:46:26,501 --> 01:46:28,594
No. No, he didn't.

1466
01:46:32,807 --> 01:46:36,038
Thank you. Thank you.

1467
01:47:35,703 --> 01:47:38,604
"This child's life was not in vain.

1468
01:47:39,507 --> 01:47:42,772
He brought us together
in a common bond of sadness.

1469
01:47:43,377 --> 01:47:46,175
He reminded us
how human we are...

1470
01:47:47,114 --> 01:47:50,811
...and how hurt and pain
touches us all.

1471
01:47:51,485 --> 01:47:56,422
Go to God, little angel.
And thank you."

1472
01:48:22,216 --> 01:48:24,912
I really appreciate you bringing
me out here, Bobby.

1473
01:48:25,086 --> 01:48:26,883
I truly do.

